<DOC><DOCNO> AP900209-0197 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-09-90 2145EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Norway-Namibia     02-09 0099</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Norway-Namibia,0101</SECOND><HEAD>Norway to Drop Economic Sanctions of Namibia</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Namibia</HEAD><DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Norway will drop its trade embargo and othersanctions against Namibia as the nation becomes indepedent of SouthAfrica, the government announced Friday.   Parliamentary approval for lifting the trade ban is expected intime for Namibia's first day of freedom, March 31, the ForeignMinistry said in a statement.   Sanctions were expanded in March 1987 to put pressure on SouthAfrica's apartheid system of legalized segregation and whiteminority rule. Namibia was included in the boycott because it wasoccupied by South Africa.</TEXT></DOC>